00:00:52,422 --> 00:00:55,991
   narrator: in the first half  
      of the 20th century,      

9
00:00:55,993 --> 00:00:57,225
         power steering         
       was not an option.       

10
00:00:57,227 --> 00:01:01,162
  prototypes were too expensive 
         for production.        

11
00:01:01,164 --> 00:01:04,199
      during world war ii,      
 the british and american armies

12
00:01:04,201 --> 00:01:05,801
   began to use power steering  

13
00:01:05,803 --> 00:01:08,470
        in heavy vehicles       
       like armored cars,       

14
00:01:08,472 --> 00:01:12,007
   and auto makers soon began   
adding it to passenger vehicles.

15
00:01:14,545 --> 00:01:16,277
 these hydraulic steering pumps 

16
00:01:16,279 --> 00:01:18,947
     are the steering muscle    
         in muscle cars,        

17
00:01:18,949 --> 00:01:22,751
    providing a power assist    
to give the driver more control.

18
00:01:24,988 --> 00:01:28,691
    using computer software,    
 manufacturers design the pumps 

19
00:01:28,693 --> 00:01:31,593
         to fit specific        
      classes of vehicles.      

20
00:01:31,595 --> 00:01:34,997
   they print a plastic model   
      using a 3-d printer.      

21
00:01:34,999 --> 00:01:38,366
      this is a time-lapse      
      video of the process.     

22
00:01:38,368 --> 00:01:40,568
    the designer removes the    
 plastic model and he sends it, 

23
00:01:40,570 --> 00:01:44,906
 along with the computer design,
     to a casting facility,     

24
00:01:44,908 --> 00:01:49,078
     which produces aluminum    
       pump-housing parts.      

25
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:51,246
      back at the factory,      
         a worker mounts        

26
00:01:51,248 --> 00:01:53,248
 12 of the castings in a machine

27
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:55,351
    with computer-controlled    
            tooling.            

28
00:01:57,654 --> 00:01:59,288
    he activates the system,    

29
00:01:59,290 --> 00:02:03,592
      and it moves the rack     
   of castings into position.   

30
00:02:03,594 --> 00:02:07,196
        the tools machine       
    the face of the castings.   

31
00:02:07,198 --> 00:02:09,464
 they bore center-bearing holes 
            and drill           

32
00:02:09,466 --> 00:02:12,400
    threaded holes for bolts.   

33
00:02:12,402 --> 00:02:16,704
     this is precision work,    
which will now be double-checked

34
00:02:16,706 --> 00:02:20,342
      by a device known as      
 a coordinate measuring machine.

35
00:02:20,344 --> 00:02:24,813
    a worker clamps the pump    
     housing in the machine.    

36
00:02:24,815 --> 00:02:28,884
    then, a ruby-tipped probe   
      scans its dimensions.     

37
00:02:28,886 --> 00:02:31,553
      the machine analyzes      
        the information.        

38
00:02:31,555 --> 00:02:34,089
   it verifies that every part  
      of the housing meets      

39
00:02:34,091 --> 00:02:36,191
   the precise specifications.  

40
00:02:36,193 --> 00:02:39,228
                     ♪♪         

41
00:02:40,730 --> 00:02:45,567
     with that confirmation,    
      he unclamps the part.     

42
00:02:45,569 --> 00:02:48,904
 this is the pump housing in the
  various stages of production. 

43
00:02:48,906 --> 00:02:52,540
                     ♪♪         

44
00:02:52,542 --> 00:02:55,043
    other tools turn a solid    
         aluminum dowel         

45
00:02:55,045 --> 00:02:58,180
       into a fitting for       
    the pump's pressure bore.   

46
00:02:58,182 --> 00:02:59,982
  they sculpt the circumference 

47
00:02:59,984 --> 00:03:03,017
       and carve a complex      
     geometry in the center     

48
00:03:03,019 --> 00:03:07,522
    for controlling the flow    
    of power steering fluid.    

49
00:03:07,524 --> 00:03:10,258
 another tool carves the thread 
      to screw the fitting      

50
00:03:10,260 --> 00:03:11,760
     into the pressure bore,    

51
00:03:11,762 --> 00:03:14,663
    and the final one drills    
     the fluid bypass hole.     

52
00:03:14,665 --> 00:03:19,634
     a blue anodized coating    
   protects it from corrosion.  

53
00:03:19,636 --> 00:03:22,504
   a worker now locks the pump  
  housing in a honing machine.  

54
00:03:22,506 --> 00:03:25,841
 the machine floods the pressure
   relief bore with lubricant   

55
00:03:25,843 --> 00:03:32,146
  as the stone hones the inner  
diameter to a precise tolerance.

56
00:03:32,148 --> 00:03:35,717
   he then transfers the pump   
       housing to a press.      

57
00:03:35,719 --> 00:03:38,586
 he inserts a bearing and shaft 
       in the center bore.      

58
00:03:38,588 --> 00:03:42,991
   he places an aluminum tool   
   over the bearing and shaft   

59
00:03:42,993 --> 00:03:44,660
     to align them correctly    

60
00:03:44,662 --> 00:03:48,664
     as he manually presses     
       them into the bore.      

61
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:51,232
    once the bearing has been   
       solidly entrenched,      

62
00:03:51,234 --> 00:03:53,535
      he removes the tool.      

63
00:03:53,537 --> 00:03:56,138
       he inserts a metal       
      snap ring in a groove     

64
00:03:56,140 --> 00:04:00,108
to retain the bearing and shaft.

65
00:04:00,110 --> 00:04:03,778
he turns the power steering pump
    over an installs o-rings    

66
00:04:03,780 --> 00:04:05,714
  to seal the pressure section. 

67
00:04:05,716 --> 00:04:09,451
                     ♪♪         

68
00:04:09,453 --> 00:04:11,953
         then the worker        
      installs the cam ring     

69
00:04:11,955 --> 00:04:15,757
  and the rotor with the veins. 

70
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:19,061
       as the rotor spins,      
 the veins will move in and out,

71
00:04:19,063 --> 00:04:20,662
   collecting hydraulic fluid.  

72
00:04:20,664 --> 00:04:22,597
   this process adds pressure,  

73
00:04:22,599 --> 00:04:25,466
       taking the load off      
       the steering wheel.      

74
00:04:25,468 --> 00:04:28,069
       the worker installs      
   this critical sub-assembly   

75
00:04:28,071 --> 00:04:31,539
      in the pump housing.      

76
00:04:31,541 --> 00:04:34,609
  he screws the device in place 
      in the four corners.      

77
00:04:34,611 --> 00:04:38,447
                     ♪♪         

78
00:04:38,449 --> 00:04:40,715
       he turns the power       
       steering pump over       

79
00:04:40,717 --> 00:04:41,716
        and seals the end       
      of the pressure bore      

80
00:04:41,718 --> 00:04:45,520
      with an aluminum plug     
       and copper washer.       

81
00:04:45,522 --> 00:04:48,557
                     ♪♪         

82
00:04:51,561 --> 00:04:53,561
    he now tucks the pressure   
          relief valve          

83
00:04:53,563 --> 00:04:57,733
        in the open part        
      of the pressure bore.     

84
00:04:57,735 --> 00:04:59,868
 he secures it with the special 
          flow fitting          

85
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:02,137
   we saw machined earlier on.  

86
00:05:02,139 --> 00:05:06,607
                     ♪♪         

87
00:05:06,609 --> 00:05:09,111
     he tightens the fitting    
      with a torque wrench.     

88
00:05:10,547 --> 00:05:14,650
       he turns the power       
  steering pump onto its side.  

89
00:05:16,786 --> 00:05:18,987
      he attaches a fitting     
       to the intake port       

90
00:05:18,989 --> 00:05:20,989
    for the hydraulic fluid.    

91
00:05:20,991 --> 00:05:22,991
     the power steering pump    
         is now equipped        

92
00:05:22,993 --> 00:05:24,860
   with all the working parts.  

93
00:05:27,464 --> 00:05:28,963
        here's a look at        
       the transformation.      

94
00:05:28,965 --> 00:05:33,502
  a display model with a cutout 
      offers a peak inside.     

95
00:05:35,539 --> 00:05:36,771
      at the test station,      

96
00:05:36,773 --> 00:05:37,939
       a technician makes       
       all the connections      

97
00:05:37,941 --> 00:05:42,610
    and runs it as if it was    
      in an actual racecar.     

98
00:05:42,612 --> 00:05:45,614
     a computer measures its    
    performance and confirms    

99
00:05:45,616 --> 00:05:49,717
        that it meets all       
   the technical requirements.  

100
00:05:49,719 --> 00:05:52,487
     the power steering pump    
   is now ready for the twists  

101
00:05:52,489 --> 00:05:55,056
          and turns of          
      professional racing.      

102
00:05:55,058 --> 00:05:58,060
                     ♪♪         

103
00:06:11,341 --> 00:06:13,374
     narrator: across asia,     
         rice bowl meals        

104
00:06:13,376 --> 00:06:14,409
   are an enduring tradition.   

105
00:06:14,411 --> 00:06:16,778
      by combining protein      
     and vegetable elements     

106
00:06:16,780 --> 00:06:20,782
      with rice in a bowl,      
       people have a meal.      

107
00:06:20,784 --> 00:06:22,517
    it's asian comfort food,    

108
00:06:22,519 --> 00:06:24,119
   and somehow it just tastes   
        better in a bowl.       

109
00:06:24,121 --> 00:06:27,289
   and people around the world  
         are discovering        

110
00:06:27,291 --> 00:06:29,992
       the appeal of these      
         one-bowl meals.        

111
00:06:32,296 --> 00:06:35,097
        asian bowl meals        
      start with the rice.      

112
00:06:35,099 --> 00:06:37,265
         then people add        
       whatever they want.      

113
00:06:37,267 --> 00:06:42,170
     at food bars like this,    
 there's any number of choices. 

114
00:06:42,172 --> 00:06:44,740
the bowls can be served up fast,
    and the food is healthy.    

115
00:06:44,742 --> 00:06:48,543
     because there are many     
     possible combinations,     

116
00:06:48,545 --> 00:06:52,013
      these one-bowl meals      
        never get boring.       

117
00:06:52,015 --> 00:06:54,715
       preparations start       
         with the rice.         

118
00:06:54,717 --> 00:06:58,820
    this food worker measures   
     enough for 40 portions.    

119
00:06:58,822 --> 00:07:01,156
    after rinsing the grains    
           repeatedly,          

120
00:07:01,158 --> 00:07:03,358
  he adds it to a rice cooker.  

121
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:08,262
   he then measures the water   
          for cooking.          

122
00:07:08,264 --> 00:07:10,298
    he adds it to the cooker.   

123
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:15,237
it will steam the grains so they
  cook uniformly for one hour.  

124
00:07:15,239 --> 00:07:17,639
   while the rice is cooking,   
         the food worker        

125
00:07:17,641 --> 00:07:21,443
 then pours peeled garlic cloves
     into a food processor.     

126
00:07:23,413 --> 00:07:25,947
       he adds a half cup       
        of vegetable oil.       

127
00:07:25,949 --> 00:07:29,618
 the garlic will flavor several 
  dishes in the asian food bar. 

128
00:07:32,256 --> 00:07:37,292
  the food processor chops the  
  garlic to a fine consistency. 

129
00:07:37,294 --> 00:07:39,627
        using a mandolin        
        vegetable slicer,       

130
00:07:39,629 --> 00:07:43,264
  he slices slivers of carrots. 

131
00:07:43,266 --> 00:07:44,900
   along with chopped onions,   

132
00:07:44,902 --> 00:07:48,403
    the carrots will enhance    
    the flavor of fried rice.   

133
00:07:48,405 --> 00:07:50,672
    he now removes some rice    
        from the cooker,        

134
00:07:50,674 --> 00:07:51,872
  in order to make fried rice.  

135
00:07:51,874 --> 00:07:56,511
     he separates the grains    
 so they'll fry more uniformly. 

136
00:07:56,513 --> 00:08:00,048
                     ♪♪         

137
00:08:00,050 --> 00:08:01,549
         the food worker        
      is now ready to fry.      

138
00:08:01,551 --> 00:08:05,820
        he heats the wok        
   to a very high temperature.  

139
00:08:05,822 --> 00:08:10,325
      he adds cooking oil,      
    and it starts to sizzle.    

140
00:08:10,327 --> 00:08:12,393
he tosses in the carrot slivers,

141
00:08:12,395 --> 00:08:15,864
      chopped onion, garlic     
        and frozen peas.        

142
00:08:15,866 --> 00:08:18,300
       he constantly stirs      
        the ingredients,        

143
00:08:18,302 --> 00:08:22,370
         and the flavors        
       sweeten and deepen.      

144
00:08:22,372 --> 00:08:24,605
     he turns down the heat     
     a bit an adds the rice.    

145
00:08:24,607 --> 00:08:28,810
he mixes the rice with the other
   ingredients as the cooking   

146
00:08:28,812 --> 00:08:33,248
          continues at          
  a slightly lower temperature. 

147
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:35,049
  he measures the temperature.  

148
00:08:35,051 --> 00:08:36,551
    for food safety reasons,    

149
00:08:36,553 --> 00:08:41,255
       it needs to be over      
     143 degrees fahrenheit.    

150
00:08:41,257 --> 00:08:44,559
 the food worker pours soy sauce
        onto the hot wok.       

151
00:08:44,561 --> 00:08:46,728
        it trickles down        
      to permeate the rice,     

152
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:49,130
    adding flavor and color.    

153
00:08:49,132 --> 00:08:52,366
  that completes the fried rice 
   component of the food bar.   

154
00:08:52,368 --> 00:08:56,371
    next up are the vegetable   
      and protein choices.      

155
00:08:58,142 --> 00:09:01,309
      the food worker cubes     
        sushi-grade tuna.       

156
00:09:01,311 --> 00:09:04,712
      it will be marinated      
   with a spicy saucy shortly.  

157
00:09:04,714 --> 00:09:07,315
       he places the tuna       
    in a food bar container.    

158
00:09:09,386 --> 00:09:11,386
        he peels cucumber       
     and then juliennes it.     

159
00:09:11,388 --> 00:09:14,623
   the cucumber will be a raw   
           food choice          

160
00:09:14,625 --> 00:09:17,492
        that will offset        
 the strong flavor of the tuna. 

161
00:09:19,763 --> 00:09:23,798
  the food worker then prepares 
   the tuna's spicy marinade.   

162
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,367
       he adds chili sauce      

163
00:09:25,369 --> 00:09:30,304
      and a smaller amount      
   of chili oil to mayonnaise.  

164
00:09:30,306 --> 00:09:32,273
         it's hot stuff.        

165
00:09:32,275 --> 00:09:35,377
                     ♪♪         

166
00:09:35,379 --> 00:09:38,379
      a seaweed salad dish      
  is another refreshing choice  

167
00:09:38,381 --> 00:09:41,216
   that will cool the palate.   

168
00:09:41,218 --> 00:09:45,453
        he adds the chili       
     mayonnaise to the tuna.    

169
00:09:45,455 --> 00:09:47,188
    and he turns up the heat    
          a little more         

170
00:09:47,190 --> 00:09:49,324
   with some extra chili oil.   

171
00:09:52,262 --> 00:09:55,563
  a thorough mixing completely  
     saturates the raw fish     

172
00:09:55,565 --> 00:09:58,700
      with the spicy sauce.     

173
00:09:58,702 --> 00:10:01,069
      next, the food worker     
      prepares the dressing     

174
00:10:01,071 --> 00:10:02,870
      for a cabbage salad.      

175
00:10:02,872 --> 00:10:05,474
         he starts with         
       a white miso paste.      

176
00:10:05,476 --> 00:10:07,541
        a generous amount       
      of soy sauce follows.     

177
00:10:07,543 --> 00:10:12,013
 sushi vinegar and vegetable oil
    are the next ingredients.   

178
00:10:12,015 --> 00:10:16,917
  after adding some sesame oil, 
  he blends all the components. 

179
00:10:16,919 --> 00:10:20,555
  he coats the shredded cabbage 
     with the miso dressing.    

180
00:10:20,557 --> 00:10:25,227
 he sprinkles black sesame seeds
     onto the cabbage salad.    

181
00:10:28,031 --> 00:10:31,799
          teriyaki beef         
       is the next option.      

182
00:10:31,801 --> 00:10:35,436
 the main ingredients are shaved
  filet steak, chopped ginger,  

183
00:10:35,438 --> 00:10:37,238
       and shredded onion.      

184
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:39,673
the food worker sautés the onion
           and ginger           

185
00:10:39,675 --> 00:10:42,944
    to provide a flavor base.   

186
00:10:42,946 --> 00:10:46,014
    he adds the shaved steak,   
        and as it cooks,        

187
00:10:46,016 --> 00:10:48,850
     it takes up the essence    
    of the onion and ginger.    

188
00:10:48,852 --> 00:10:51,920
                     ♪♪         

189
00:10:53,490 --> 00:10:55,222
  the soy-based teriyaki sauce  

190
00:10:55,224 --> 00:10:57,826
            provides            
   the final layer of flavor.   

191
00:10:59,496 --> 00:11:04,532
  with this dish now complete,  
  it's time for the fun part -- 

192
00:11:04,534 --> 00:11:08,203
 mixing and matching components 
    for the asian food bowl.    

193
00:11:23,687 --> 00:11:26,253
   narrator: there was a time   
  when an elegant walking cane  

194
00:11:26,255 --> 00:11:29,123
       was a status symbol      
   for fashionable gentlemen.   

195
00:11:29,125 --> 00:11:32,594
   today, a cane is no longer   
    considered an accessory,    

196
00:11:32,596 --> 00:11:35,130
    but rather a utilitarian    
           medical aid          

197
00:11:35,132 --> 00:11:37,231
for people with mobility issues.

198
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:39,700
        however, one can        
        still find canes        

199
00:11:39,702 --> 00:11:42,204
       which combine both       
      function and fashion.     

200
00:11:43,673 --> 00:11:46,608
    walking canes can indeed    
           be stylish,          

201
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:50,545
 with straight or crook handles 
  made of exotic wood or bone,  

202
00:11:50,547 --> 00:11:54,782
      elegant knob handles,     
or elaborate figurative handles.

203
00:11:54,784 --> 00:11:57,084
     this family enterprise     
     has been hand-crafting     

204
00:11:57,086 --> 00:12:01,188
    walking canes since 1909.   

205
00:12:01,190 --> 00:12:06,094
 making a crook handle requires 
  bending the handle material.  

206
00:12:06,096 --> 00:12:09,163
  after heating a curved steel  
         form in a fire,        

207
00:12:09,165 --> 00:12:12,801
  workers insert a square stick 
   of ebony in a steel spring   

208
00:12:12,803 --> 00:12:16,271
   and mount it on the central  
      axis of the machine.      

209
00:12:16,273 --> 00:12:19,407
     the clamp the machine's    
  guide wheel against the form, 

210
00:12:19,409 --> 00:12:22,644
then clamp the part of the stick
   that will remain straight.   

211
00:12:25,815 --> 00:12:27,482
    using their body weight,    

212
00:12:27,484 --> 00:12:30,284
      the worker forces the     
    machine's lever forward,    

213
00:12:30,286 --> 00:12:31,853
      wrapping the top part     
          of the stick          

214
00:12:31,855 --> 00:12:34,122
         around the hot,        
          curved form.          

215
00:12:34,124 --> 00:12:37,158
                     ♪♪         

216
00:12:39,095 --> 00:12:42,029
 it's critical to do this slowly
       to prevent the wood      

217
00:12:42,031 --> 00:12:44,566
         from snapping.         

218
00:12:47,003 --> 00:12:50,905
workers then lock the bent stick
against the form with a brace...

219
00:12:53,876 --> 00:12:55,877
 and remove it from the machine.

220
00:12:55,879 --> 00:12:58,913
                     ♪♪         

221
00:13:00,917 --> 00:13:04,018
  they set it aside for a week. 

222
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:08,289
   one week later, they remove  
      the brace and spring      

223
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:09,990
      and mount the curved      
        stick on a lathe.       

224
00:13:09,992 --> 00:13:13,661
       as the stick spins,      
   a carriage moves a saw down  

225
00:13:13,663 --> 00:13:18,133
 the straight part of the cane, 
       known as the shaft,      

226
00:13:18,135 --> 00:13:21,036
      reducing the diameter     
      and rounding it out.      

227
00:13:23,239 --> 00:13:26,340
    this is the shaft before    
      and after this step.      

228
00:13:26,342 --> 00:13:29,377
                     ♪♪         

229
00:13:32,915 --> 00:13:36,884
    a worker runs the handle    
      against a coarse grit     

230
00:13:36,886 --> 00:13:40,822
  sanding belt to pare it down  
   and begin rounding it out.   

231
00:13:42,659 --> 00:13:47,161
   he uses a router to refine   
   the shape and works on the   

232
00:13:47,163 --> 00:13:50,131
     harder-to-access inner     
       part of the curve.       

233
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:53,168
                     ♪♪         

234
00:13:54,171 --> 00:13:54,903
   once the handle is rounded,  

235
00:13:54,905 --> 00:13:58,506
     and its diameter equal     
      to that of the shaft,     

236
00:13:58,508 --> 00:14:01,042
           he performs          
      a final fine sanding.     

237
00:14:01,044 --> 00:14:04,079
                     ♪♪         

238
00:14:11,754 --> 00:14:15,656
then he polishes the entire cane
     with polishing compound    

239
00:14:15,658 --> 00:14:17,992
 against a cotton buffing wheel.

240
00:14:17,994 --> 00:14:20,995
                     ♪♪         

241
00:14:22,999 --> 00:14:27,468
  slowly but surely, this makes 
  the ebony sleek and lustrous. 

242
00:14:27,470 --> 00:14:30,472
                     ♪♪         

243
00:14:31,974 --> 00:14:34,842
       all wooden canes --      
 these here are made of maple --

244
00:14:34,844 --> 00:14:38,379
 warp a bit during woodworking. 

245
00:14:38,381 --> 00:14:41,916
  another worker heats the cane 
   to make the wood flexible,   

246
00:14:41,918 --> 00:14:44,952
         then inserts it        
      in a v-shaped holder      

247
00:14:44,954 --> 00:14:47,155
         and peers down         
     the length of the shaft    

248
00:14:47,157 --> 00:14:50,024
     to assess the direction    
        of the deformity.       

249
00:14:50,026 --> 00:14:52,761
        then he manually        
    straightens out the cane.   

250
00:14:54,264 --> 00:15:00,101
these canes undergo a final step
  to add a decorative feature.  

251
00:15:00,103 --> 00:15:02,937
  a worker sands off some wood  
      on the crook handle,      

252
00:15:02,939 --> 00:15:04,972
 creating a flat, oval surface. 

253
00:15:04,974 --> 00:15:10,011
he applies glue, then he adheres
      a piece of cow horn.      

254
00:15:11,981 --> 00:15:13,714
      once the glue dries,      

255
00:15:13,716 --> 00:15:16,651
    he grinds the horn flush    
   with the surrounding wood.   

256
00:15:16,653 --> 00:15:19,721
                     ♪♪         

257
00:15:21,958 --> 00:15:24,392
   the result is a horn inlay.  

258
00:15:26,863 --> 00:15:28,696
          wooden canes          
      also need protection      

259
00:15:28,698 --> 00:15:31,332
   against moisture and wear.   

260
00:15:31,334 --> 00:15:34,835
   the factory submerges them   
   in varnish for a half hour,  

261
00:15:34,837 --> 00:15:36,804
       so that the varnish      
        deeply penetrates       

262
00:15:36,806 --> 00:15:38,906
     the pores of the wood.     

263
00:15:38,908 --> 00:15:43,678
    hanging the canes to dry    
 would leave varnish drip marks,

264
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:46,514
    so the factory uses this    
     ingenious pulley-driven    

265
00:15:46,516 --> 00:15:51,052
   contraption that dates back  
          to the 1900s.         

266
00:15:51,054 --> 00:15:53,387
      with its wood wheels      
       and leather belts,       

267
00:15:53,389 --> 00:15:56,624
    the machine continuously    
        rotates the canes       

268
00:15:56,626 --> 00:16:00,261
   to prevent the wet varnish   
 from dripping as it air dries. 

269
00:16:03,165 --> 00:16:05,099
       that's how to make       
  a wooden crook-handled cane.  

270
00:16:05,101 --> 00:16:08,936
       as you'll see next,      
      fancier walking canes     

271
00:16:08,938 --> 00:16:10,939
    require additional steps.   

272
00:16:25,488 --> 00:16:28,523
narrator: whether it's decorated
   with ornately carved wood,   

273
00:16:28,525 --> 00:16:33,127
  sleek horn or gleaning metal, 
brandishing a fancy walking cane

274
00:16:33,129 --> 00:16:36,030
         is like wearing        
   a bold pair of eyeglasses.   

275
00:16:36,032 --> 00:16:38,766
      what might otherwise      
      be a bland necessity      

276
00:16:38,768 --> 00:16:41,469
         can be elevated        
     to a fashion statement.    

277
00:16:45,308 --> 00:16:48,342
     elegant canes can have     
      horn or knob handles,     

278
00:16:48,344 --> 00:16:51,479
        or silver-plated        
        figural handles.        

279
00:16:51,481 --> 00:16:55,082
   the figural ones are molded  
         two at a time.         

280
00:16:55,084 --> 00:16:58,185
      after placing a screw     
    mechanism in each cavity,   

281
00:16:58,187 --> 00:16:59,954
    a worker closes the mold    

282
00:16:59,956 --> 00:17:02,890
        and places it in        
      a centrifuge machine.     

283
00:17:02,892 --> 00:17:07,094
       as the mold spins,       
 he ladles pewter into a funnel 

284
00:17:07,096 --> 00:17:10,931
 that feeds the channels leading
    into the mould cavities.    

285
00:17:10,933 --> 00:17:14,368
  the centrifugal force shoots  
the pewter onto the cavity walls

286
00:17:14,370 --> 00:17:16,236
        in an even layer,       

287
00:17:16,238 --> 00:17:19,807
  where it cools and solidifies 
     in about five minutes.     

288
00:17:19,809 --> 00:17:24,044
    then he stops the machine   
     and removes the mould.     

289
00:17:24,046 --> 00:17:26,380
    the worker opens the mold   
          and extracts          

290
00:17:26,382 --> 00:17:28,416
    the two pewter castings,    

291
00:17:28,418 --> 00:17:33,220
 each with it's screw mechanism 
       securely embedded.       

292
00:17:33,222 --> 00:17:35,556
     one is a cobra handle.     

293
00:17:35,558 --> 00:17:37,959
       the other is a dog       
        and boar handle.        

294
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:41,529
          they require          
      a bit of refinement,      

295
00:17:41,531 --> 00:17:45,233
       so the next step is      
   to remove the excess metal   

296
00:17:45,235 --> 00:17:47,468
   with a rotating wire brush.  

297
00:17:49,872 --> 00:17:51,839
      a worker then shines      
         up the surface         

298
00:17:51,841 --> 00:17:53,674
  with some polishing compound  

299
00:17:53,676 --> 00:17:55,676
   and a cloth buffing wheel.   

300
00:17:55,678 --> 00:17:58,713
                     ♪♪         

301
00:18:01,184 --> 00:18:03,517
        he washes off the       
       polishing compound       

302
00:18:03,519 --> 00:18:05,486
  and silver-plates the pewter. 

303
00:18:07,557 --> 00:18:12,994
 the handle will top an equally 
      elegant ebony shaft.      

304
00:18:12,996 --> 00:18:15,963
a worker places the square stick
      of ebony in a lathe,      

305
00:18:15,965 --> 00:18:17,798
        which rounds it.        

306
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:20,835
                     ♪♪         

307
00:18:24,074 --> 00:18:27,842
 the shaft goes through several 
  sanding and polishing steps.  

308
00:18:29,912 --> 00:18:33,314
      then a worker drills      
      a two-inch-deep hole      

309
00:18:33,316 --> 00:18:34,849
        in the top of it.       

310
00:18:39,088 --> 00:18:42,390
  he puts some glue in the hole 
    and screws in the handle.   

311
00:18:42,392 --> 00:18:45,460
                     ♪♪         

312
00:18:49,232 --> 00:18:52,300
     if silver-plated cobras    
       aren't your style,       

313
00:18:52,302 --> 00:18:54,836
       how about a handle       
     made of white cow horn?    

314
00:18:54,838 --> 00:19:00,341
  first, a worker heats all but 
 the tip of the horn in a fire. 

315
00:19:00,343 --> 00:19:04,212
 this destroy the nerves in the 
  bone inside the horn's shell. 

316
00:19:06,216 --> 00:19:07,782
    this horn will be shaped    
      into a crooked handle     

317
00:19:07,784 --> 00:19:11,218
 using the same bending machine 
         the workers use        

318
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:13,788
     for wood crook handles.    

319
00:19:13,790 --> 00:19:14,655
  the base of the horn is hot,  

320
00:19:14,657 --> 00:19:20,394
    so they use a small block   
      of wood as a buffer.      

321
00:19:20,396 --> 00:19:22,463
  after clamping the machine's  
           guide wheel          

322
00:19:22,465 --> 00:19:24,498
 against the middle of the horn,

323
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:28,202
   they use their body weight   
   to move the lever forward,   

324
00:19:28,204 --> 00:19:31,539
  and wrap the top half of the  
  horn against the curved form. 

325
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:34,575
                     ♪♪         

326
00:19:39,048 --> 00:19:41,415
    before heating the horn,    
       the worker drilled       

327
00:19:41,417 --> 00:19:43,183
  a small hole through its tip. 

328
00:19:43,185 --> 00:19:48,122
now he inserts a thin steel wire
   through that hole and ties   

329
00:19:48,124 --> 00:19:50,657
     the wire tightly around    
        the opposite side       

330
00:19:50,659 --> 00:19:53,227
        to hold the horn        
       to the round form.       

331
00:19:53,229 --> 00:19:55,296
  he sets it aside for a week.  

332
00:19:57,466 --> 00:20:02,102
a horn handle undergoes the same
   multi-step sanding process   

333
00:20:02,104 --> 00:20:04,705
   as a wood handle, however,   

334
00:20:04,707 --> 00:20:07,107
         a worker drills        
     a hole into the bottom     

335
00:20:07,109 --> 00:20:09,610
 and screws in an aluminum rod. 

336
00:20:09,612 --> 00:20:12,980
  this makes the handle easier  
     to hold while sanding.     

337
00:20:12,982 --> 00:20:16,017
                     ♪♪         

338
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:19,887
  the worker removes the final  
    traces of the outer layer   

339
00:20:19,889 --> 00:20:24,758
   with a router and finalizes  
       the crook's shape.       

340
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:27,795
                     ♪♪         

341
00:20:33,969 --> 00:20:35,369
      he removes the handle     
       from the metal rod       

342
00:20:35,371 --> 00:20:40,007
       and finishes it off      
      with a fine sanding.      

343
00:20:40,009 --> 00:20:42,843
     the horn surface is now    
       as smooth as silk.       

344
00:20:42,845 --> 00:20:45,880
                     ♪♪         

345
00:20:50,286 --> 00:20:52,453
   he then polishes the handle  
    on a cotton buffing wheel   

346
00:20:52,455 --> 00:20:57,625
   using a polishing compound   
 specially formulated for horn. 

347
00:21:00,130 --> 00:21:03,597
         that brings out        
      the color and sheen.      

348
00:21:03,599 --> 00:21:06,000
     then the worker screws     
      and exotic-wood shaft     

349
00:21:06,002 --> 00:21:08,869
       into the same hole       
     used for the metal rod.    

350
00:21:08,871 --> 00:21:14,475
this fashionable cane, which has
    taken 4-6 hours to craft,   

351
00:21:14,477 --> 00:21:17,211
     is ready to be modeled     
         on the walkway.        

